Mix oil, melted chocolate, and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Blend in egg substitute or egg whites a little bit at a time. Blend in vanilla. Stir in salt, baking powder, and flour into oil mixture. Chill several hours or overnight. Drop teaspoonfuls of dough into confectioners' sugar. Roll in sugar, then shape into balls. Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in the confectioners' sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Do not overbake.